          <title>Rain in Florida leads Tigers to cancel first spring home game since 2016, other games altered</title>
          <description><![CDATA[The Detroit Tigers canceled their first home spring training game since 2016 on Monday because of rain that was forecast to continue throughout the day. Detroit was supposed to play Toronto in Lakeland, Florida, but the game was called off several hours before the scheduled first pitch at 1:05 p.m.]]></description>
